---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Custom Deck Design & Construction | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Custom composite decks in Montgomery County, MD — engineered, permitted, and inspected. $40,000–$75,000+ typical. A two-visit design process ending in drawings and a fixed price."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Custom Decks · $40,000–$75,000+</p>
      <h1>Designed around how you actually live outside.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Dinners for twelve or quiet coffee for two — the way you use your yard drives the
        design more than anything. Our custom builds start with that conversation and end
        with an engineered, permitted, inspected deck built to outlast its warranty.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>The two-visit design process</h2>
      <table>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <th>Visit 1 — Design consultation</th>
            <td>We walk the site together: how you'll use the space, sight lines, sun, grade, setbacks, and HOA constraints. We measure, photograph, and align on material direction and a realistic budget range — out loud, no games.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <th>Visit 2 — Design &amp; price presentation</th>
            <td>About a week later, at your table: the design, the drawings, and three complete configurations priced exactly. Both decision-makers, one conversation, every question answered in person.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>How we build</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Montgomery County building permit pulled by us, permit fees included; HOA architectural documents prepared</li>
        <li>Miss Utility locates before any digging</li>
        <li>Footings dug to 30″ below grade — below frost line, sized to county code — with the county footing inspection passed before pour</li>
        <li>Pressure-treated 6x6 posts on galvanized standoff bases; ledger bolted to the house framing with full flashing behind it</li>
        <li>Joists at 12″ on center; every code connector installed — hangers, hurricane ties, and lateral hold-downs tying the deck to the house</li>
        <li>County framing inspection passed before a single board goes down</li>
        <li>Joist tape, premium boards with hidden fasteners, picture-frame border, PVC fascia</li>
        <li>Code-compliant stairs with illuminated stairways where selected</li>
        <li>Final county inspection passed, site cleaned, debris hauled</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Same structure, every tier</h2>
      <p>
        Good, better, and best differ in boards, railings, and details — never in the
        structure. We don't tier the safety, and we'll show you exactly what that means
        standing under your own deck.
      </p>
      <p><a class="btn primary" href="/contact">Book a design consultation</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
